<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 18 at 2:13PM CST  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...Blowing and Drifting Snow Possible This Afternoon...
Southwest winds of 20 to 30 MPH with gusts up to 35 MPH this
afternoon may cause snow that fell yesterday to blow and drift
across area roadways and reduce visibility, especially in open
area, and cause roads to become slick. A cold front will move
across the region this evening and switch the winds to the
northwest with gusts up to 40 MPH which cause blowing and drifting
to continue into this evening.
If traveling this afternoon or tonight, use caution and allow
extra time to travel.</description>
